\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 196.        LEMNACEAE}
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. D.H. Valentine. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Small aquatic perennial herbs. Fronds floating or submerged, flowering at the surface of the water, multiplying by buds from one median or two lateral pouches, the new fronds separating or remaining linked. Roots simple, on the ventral surface of the fronds, or absent. Inflorescence minute, consisting of 1 stamen and 1 ovary in a cavity on the dorsal surface of the frond, or 2 stamens and 1 ovary enclosed in a sheath and in a bud-pouch. Ovary 1-locular; style short, undivided; ovules 1-4, basal. Fruit a utricle; seeds 1-4.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 All the species of the family are found in fresh water.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  Literature: C. den Hartog & F. van der Plas,{\i  Blumea }{\b 18}: 355-368 (1970).
