\pard\f0\fs28 Fronds more than 1 mm, floating or submerged, separate or connected, symmetrical or asymmetrical, flat or slightly swollen, rarely inflated; roots one per frond or absent; veins 1-3(-5). Bud-pouches 2, lateral. Raphides present. Inflorescence consisting of 2 stamens and 1 ovary enclosed in a sheath and in one of the two bud-pouches. Anthers 2-locular, dehiscing transversely. Ovary globose; ovules 1 or 4-6, orthotropous to anatropous. Fruit more or less globose; seeds longitudinally ribbed, rarely smooth.
