\pard\f0\fs28 Fronds floating, separate or 2-5 connected, flat to inflated, asymmetrical, with an inferior scale and a superior fugacious scale 3- to 15-veined; roots 2-18 on each frond, rarely absent. Bud-pouches 2, lateral. Rhaphides present. Inflorescence consisting of 2 stamens and 1 ovary enclosed in a sheath and in one of the two bud-pouches. Anthers 2-locular, dehiscing transversely. Ovary globose; ovules 1 or 2-4, orthotropous to anatropous. Fruit more or less globose; seeds longitudinally ribbed or smooth.
\par

